# MeetMinder — Privacy Policy

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

MeetMinder is a Chrome extension that shows your upcoming Google Calendar meetings in the browser toolbar so you never miss one. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data collection

MeetMinder does **not** collect, store, transmit or share any personal data with third parties.

## How it works

- You sign in with your Google account using OAuth2
- MeetMinder fetches today's calendar events from the Google Calendar API and caches them temporarily in `chrome.storage.local` on your device only
- Calendar data is refreshed every 5 minutes in the background
- Your notification timing preference is saved locally in `chrome.storage.sync` and never leaves your device
- No calendar data or personal information is ever sent to any external server other than Google's own APIs

## Permissions

| Permission | Reason |
|---|---|
| `identity` | To authenticate with Google via OAuth2 |
| `storage` | To cache calendar events and save your notification preference |
| `alarms` | To refresh calendar data every 5 minutes and trigger meeting notifications |
| `notifications` | To show a browser notification before a meeting starts |

## Google API access

MeetMinder requests the following Google OAuth scope:

| Scope | Reason |
|---|---|
| `calendar.readonly` | To read today's calendar events |

## Revoking access

Sign out at any time using the Sign out button in the popup. To fully revoke access, visit [myaccount.google.com/permissions](https://myaccount.google.com/permissions) and remove MeetMinder.

